<section id="faq">
  <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
  <FaqItem question="Can you really make money online with just a phone, no computer?">
    <p>Yes. Survey apps, cash-back apps, marketplace selling, and even content-based affiliate marketing can all be done entirely from a phone. The ceiling is lower for pure task-apps and higher for content-based methods, but neither requires a computer at any step.</p>
  </FaqItem>
  <FaqItem question="What's the most realistic amount to earn from money-making apps?">
    <p>Most task and survey apps produce $20–$100 a month with consistent use. That's genuinely realistic, not a lowball — treating these apps as a full income replacement is where expectations go wrong, not the apps themselves.</p>
  </FaqItem>
  <FaqItem question="Are passive income apps like Honeygain worth it?">
    <p>They're genuinely passive but genuinely low-yield — commonly $0.10–$0.30 per day per device. Worth having running in the background if you're not relying on the income, not worth treating as a primary strategy.</p>
  </FaqItem>
  <FaqItem question="What phone-only method has the highest income ceiling?">
    <p>Content-based methods — affiliate marketing through social content, or selling on marketplace apps — have a meaningfully higher ceiling than task/survey apps, since income scales with audience or inventory rather than a fixed number of daily tasks.</p>
  </FaqItem>
  <FaqItem question="Do I need to buy anything to start earning from apps on my phone?">
    <p>No. Every method in this guide — surveys, cash-back, marketplace selling, affiliate content — has a genuinely free entry point. Any app requiring payment to access earning opportunities is a red flag, not a legitimate barrier to entry.</p>
  </FaqItem>
</section>

